comments: ["Have been using doglog for a couple years now, it's one of the few apps that I use every single day. I'd be lost without it. There've been a few bugs along the way but they are always responsive and fixed quickly. I especially like some of the recent changes to the events like the drop-down in Medicine to specify the type. It's a lifesaver for multi-carer packs & dogs with health issues, being able to easily create a log of everything to share with the vet is priceless.", "Fantastic app for monitoring your pet's day-to-day life. We had a cat with several health issues and DogLog allowed us to track her health and daily routine easily and effectively. As a result, we were fully prepared for vet appointments with a concise record of her progress and, in turn, the vet could provide more effective medical care for her. Highly recommend this all for any pet owner.", "I like the app as it is very useful to be able to quickly make notes about your dog that will be organised and sorted in a nice way so you can easily go back to it. However a few things could be improved. One thing is the weight curve. The X-axis should be your pet's age, not the number increment of your measurement. If you don't weigh your pet continuously you will not see the slopes of weight gain/loss as realistic in the time dimension.", "The application doesn't allow me to put in the breed of my dog from my profile. Also, all info I inserted got deleted the moment I pressed 'back'button even though I had saved it. I'm deleting this app and finding a working one!", "Great and simple way to track daily activities, as well as medications. I added my dogs exact medication by name (custom) and a few other things specific to her. I decided to get premium so I can view the usual time or day we do certain things, and it has really helped me plan out schedules. It's super easy to use and pretty inexpensive for the information you get access to.", "It's pretty good. I've been using it for about 1 yr now. No ads everywhere and I like that I can filter by event categories. Only problem I have is that I can't delete entries when clicking the delete button. Edit button works but not delete", "This seems like a fairly helpful app and I love that you can share with a pack. I need to monitor blood sugar checks, urine checks, etc. You can make the categories but I really need a graph like the temp feature. I'm using a diabetic pet specific app but it is not stable. If this app grows to that level I would likely pay as the other features seem solid.", 'Any useful analytical data is locked behind a premium fee that does not justify its cost. I can do the same stuff with a free Google form and spreadsheet', 'Perfect for keeping track of toilet routines. Can adapt new icons for other things to track. Very useful', "does exactly what I need it to: helps clear up confusion about who took the dog for a walk and when to help us avoid messy accidents and be aware of our pooch's schedule. the ONE reason this isn't 5 stars for me is the lack of dark mode because this app blinds me every night i take my dog for s walk. otherwise, perfect little simple app.", "Love the simplicity of the interface with the option to add more activities (repeating for a common task or once, like a skunk attack!). Tracking my 11 week old puppy for the past 2 weeks has been extremely helpful. I can see patterns in what times he eats, when we go outside, when he's most likely to have an accident. would be better if you could adjust the time of the event as you are entering it instead of defaulting to current time. Slow app loading screen can be frustrating.", 'Very user friendly interface. Simple to use. The free version has enough features to get started with what appears to be paid for optional extras, which appear useful but not essential. So, you can get started for free and add the extras later, which is nice. Non-intrusive ads too. It has been very useful for us where there are six people plus two dogs in our pack, as we can each log our shared responsibilities and keep track of things. Very useful app.', 'Great app, especially for pups with multiple caregivers so you\'re not constantly texting each other "did you walk the dog before you left?". Intuitive and the simple interface makes it easy to add entries with one hand while being dragged along by over-enthusiastic puppies! The most recent release addressed the only two things I didn\'t like about the app.', "The app is exactly what I look for to keep track of my pet's daily tasks. It has a simple interface that its easy to use. I can easily add more custom items according to my dog's needs. N easily edit items by pushing the task to left. I do like them to record it in current time, so i can calculate walk time, by tapping walk at the start n grooming(cleaning) at the end of the walk. I really hope the data in the app can extracted in later version so it can be presented in doctor's visit. Thanks!", 'Great app for tracking a new puppy\'s every move. So easy to track food, weight, bowel movements, training etc. I love the option to add a photo and "like" or comment on everything. Also easily customize your own buttons (for example, we added "rest" in addition to the "nap" option). Overall great app that we are using as a "pack" with other family members who also have a new puppy.', 'This app used to be perfect. All I needed it was to log food walks and bathroom breaks. However, since my initial download several months ago they have broken every aspect of this. It has gotten to the point where I literally cannot open a dog. I have downgraded to a version of the app from 2018 and have zero issues. I have been sending crash logs regularly in hopes that they fix these problems to no avail. I will be happy to fix my rating once stability is back. Edit 11/4/19: The update to 3.8.13 has certainly fixed my stability issues but it has introduced a new problem. On the previous versions that I was using, when logging something a popup overlay would appear in the center of the screen to select the dog and write any notes. However, now it shows a redesigned full screen page. While I do like the aesthetics of this new page, it now places the dog selection and finish button at the two farthest points from your hand, at the top. With a majority of phone screens exceeding 5.5 inches this makes maintaining the leash complex. A remedy for this could be rearranging the icons to be at the bottom and placing the add a photo button at the top considering that most stabilize photos with two hands making the reach less bothersome.', "This app is the perfect thing that we were looking for. You can create custom recurring events as buttons to reuse. We created ones for sleeping, napping, and crate time. It's really the perfect solution for tracking your dogs habits. Especially great for learning a new puppy's time between eating and eliminating, and bladder control. Thank you for creating this!", 'Been using this app for a year, since shortly after we adopted our first cat and love it! Pretty easy to learn how it works, no obtrusive ads, and a great system for sharing access to the whole family. The only thing that could make it better to me would be the ability to hide certain actions from the "Log Events" screen because I don\'t plan to use some of them for kitty, such as "water" and "pee".', "Update 1/17/23 - Suddenly cannot use the app; it won't open, despite uninsta/reinstall. :( Really like being able to log when she went potty, when she ate, etc - very helpwful if you have ADHD! I also track when we train, go for a walk, any health issues that concern me (e.g. scratching a lot), and when she takes meds. I do wish there were more icons or you could add your own, because I have to repeat them a lot for what I track because there are so few and a limited variety.", "Good but offline issues - If you're out of the house without the internet & switch to a different app, when it goes to reload, it won't, and then when you get back home again & connect to the internet, all the information you added when out the house disappears. Just lost all the walk, pee, poop, drink, eating, treats, vet appointment logs etc I made when I was out. It's very annoying. It could at least store information on my phone to sync up later if I'm offline. I subscribe too.", "Responsive developer. Definitely the best app available. I'm looking forward to the updates. Currently, no ability to enter time of events at initial entry. The log is confusing to read; maybe use the pet photos on the log also? Currently everything looks the same. My Swype keyboard does not work in the app. Maybe allow for a neutral note entry in the log. To keep track of weird occurrences in the pup's life.", "This app has been very helpful to us logging three animals activities between 4 caregivers.  It's simple to use.  My only issue thus far is that when I log an activity it auto-selects every pet, and I have to unselect all, then just select one pet.  I can see where this could be handy for larger packs that do things together. However, I would love the option to set a 'default' selection - I do most activities with just one pet at a time.  Having a preset, or having none selected to start, would save me a couple steps each time.", 'I really love this app. I always end up with orphaned kittens that people bring me, and I often do the record-keeping on paper. This is even smarter. There are options for potty going and feeding. I do wish there was a way to keep records about temperature and body weight and the option to have records for cats as well as dogs. Also, a widget of some of the info would be awesome, too. Over all, it mostly filled the requirement I need in a tracking app.', 'This app allows me to customize events as well as reminders in addition to other already programmed preset options for me and gives a lot of freedom in regards to how many events and reminders you can log at a single time. When I had a question, after emailing, I recieved an answer to my question within half an hour. I may have personally needed help but I would say this app is user friendly and simple to navigate. Very happy with it.', 'Needs a lot of work. Can\'t edit/delete a record once you submit it. Can\'t mark an accident. Have to manually enter the start time twice. No "now" button for the end time to use it like a stopwatch; you instead have to manually input the end time. Default units are arbitrary. (e.g. for "poop" it defaults to a quantity of "miles") Back button on my phone always takes me to the dog chooser screen instead of screen I was previously on. Lack of stopwatch functionality is a deal-breaker for me', 'Was charged for the trial of the premium version. Unsubscribed immediately. Have emailed the developer asking for the money to be refunded. Waiting for a response.', "It's such a brilliant app for keeping records of everything about you dog, especially useful if they are regularly poorly so you can easily track records.", "Easy to add events. Would be better if you could set the time when you're adding an event, instead of having to edit it afterwards. Super for multiple people, nice notification when someone else logs an event. Statistics aren't great. I'd like to be able to visualise the time of day she's going to the toilet, and also in relation to feed time. Would be nice if the information could be exported to csv.", 'It\'s not a bad app, but it\'s crashing all the time for me. I can\'t log anything - I need to try at least 3 times before I\'m able to log anything without the app crashing on me. Also I don\'t understand why they stopped showing the weight history that we had since day 1 of us getting a puppy. For a couple of weeks it started showing only the latest logged wright event, but now it says "No events" logged - it\'s very upsetting :( I have the latest version of the app, but it still doesn\'t work.', "It's good but the only downside is there doesn't seem to be an undo button would be a nice feature. EDIT - There is a way to delete! Thankyou support team that makes the app so much easier to use! 10/10! Really useful for keeping track of toilet training and I love the fact you can add other activities 👌 would absolutely reccomend this to my friends with pets particularly puppies", "Great app, but there is no way to edit the log entries. I made some mistakes and also want to switch the way I document the heats, but I cannot go back and edit the old entries. I would make new ones but then I would have the entry doubled, since I can't delete the old ones. I like the possibility of creating custom log categories.", 'Edit: Thanks for responding! I updated my rating. Looking forward to the new version :) . . . I wish you could delete events, edit events, and add more than three pets (I use it for my ferrets too). I also wish there was a "vet" option. Other than that, it serves its purpose and we\'re able to communicate when we bring her out and feed her with everyone in our household.', "This app is AMAZING. A few small QOL things, but completely offset by how helpful it is. I'm tracking so many things for my cat who has some issues I need to keep an eye on, and this is MUCH easier than notepad. But...... Huge banner ad appeared at the top of the app today. It's very obnoxious. Still very worth it, and I 100% support them getting some income for it. I donated through the link. But maybe if you're going to go the ad route, you could have a paid ad free version? Still 5*, but 🤞?", "Update: They fixed the crashing issue really fast! I love this app because its really easy to log what you need to. It has a lot of features to use. However my main reason for getting an app like this is to be able to predict what time my dog will go potty. I was hoping the app would do this for me, but you have to pay $40 a year for it! I can't spend that much a year. I get that the makers of this app need money too, but I wish they would let you buy individual features without a monthly cost.", "I really like this app so far. The only thing I'm not happy with is in the profile feed. There are some fields like breed and food brand that I would like to add for my pup, but you seem to have to select from a dropdown. Having a rescue mix, my breed is not on there and my food brand also doesn't appear in the list. I would like the option to either select Mix or Other. Otherwise a freetext input field would be much more useful.", "Though not a dog owner, this app is the best I've found so far for tracking feeding and other necessary reminders for caring for our cats. I would love to see this expanded to include other animal breeds!!! My only downfalls, again not a dog owner but a pet owner who needs to keep track of pet health, are that some of the profile details don't have the option to be written in (food, breed, etc.). Also, I would like to be able to delete some of the activities that I do not use (i.e. outdoor activities). Again, this app would be PERFECT if it included other animal types as well!", "This app has helped me so much with tracking everything my new puppy. It had made potty training so much easier! One of the best free apps I've tried!", "Exactly what we needed for our new puppy. Especially if one person is taking over responsibilities during the night, morning, work hours, etc., we can easily see what happened and when to anticipate the upcoming events.The only thing we wish we could figure out is how to share reminders with the whole pack. Right now it looks like it's only visable to the person creating the reminders, but we are using this feature to set upcoming vaccinations, etc. and want the whole pack to get the reminders.", 'Briefly, overall, it gets the job done. But important things just arent options. We play ALOT more then we walk but there is no button for, "play". Each picture needs to be really small which sucks. I take many pics that I cannot send. There\'s no place in the feed to write a simple written update. I have to send 2 long texts during the day to give a more detailed update. The caption with each activity has to be under 7ish words. I could write a lot more. Definitely could be better IMO...', "It's a nice app with a clean interface. I like being able to track things about my puppy's health. However, the biggest downside to me is that I can't seem to find a way to edit or delete log entries. I wanted to add notes to a log after I made it, but I haven't found a way to edit it and I can't delete it and recreate the log with notes. This seems like a major feature that is completely missing. No options to work around this defect as far as I can tell."]

title: Bumble - Citas, amigos, bizz
description: Acá empieza una nueva historia 💛 Miles de personas se registran cada día en Bumble para empezar a construir relaciones sanas, encontrar amigos y crear conexiones duraderas. Bumble es la primera app que reúne en una sola red social la posibilidad de hacer nuevas conexiones para vivir una vida positiva y productiva. Tanto si buscás citas o querés encontrar pareja, hacer nuevos amigos o ampliar tu red profesional y hacer contactos profesionales, en Bumble lo vas a encontrar todo. ¡Tomá el primer paso y hacé match hoy! Conseguí relaciones sanas a tu alrededor 🌎 Bumble es la dating app que se rige por el respeto, la igualdad y la inclusión de nuestros miembros, facilitando descubrir nuevas personas cercanas a vos. Bumble te permite hablar con solteros y solteras de otras partes del mundo, desde Argentina hasta Reino Unido, siempre estamos a tu lado para ayudarte. Podés usar Bumble de distintos modos: 💛 Bumble Date: Disfrutá del dating online de una manera segura y respetuosa, conseguí citas y encontrá el amor a través de nuestro chat y todas sus funciones. 🕺 Bumble Bff: Si acabás de llegar a una ciudad o deseás expandir tu círculo de amistades, Bumble Bff es la forma más sencilla de hacer nuevos amigos y amigas.  🤝 Bumble Bizz: ¿Buscás un nuevo reto profesional? ¿Inversionistas? ¿Hacer networking? Resumí brevemente quién sos, a qué te dedicás y qué tipo de conexión estás buscando. La vida es más fácil con Bumble 😊 Bumble es el lugar para quienes no quieren perder su tiempo y prefieren conectar con personas sinceras y positivas. Ahora, flirtear y construir relaciones resulta una tarea más agradable y menos estresante. Descubrí cómo aprovechar Bumble al máximo: - Encontrá a esa persona especial: Usá el muy completo filtro de nuestro chat para hacer amigos y amigas nuevas o para flirtear y encontrar tu media naranja 🍊 - Destacá tu perfil: Con Spotlight 🔅 mostramos tu perfil a más miembros cerca de tu área durante 30 minutos, para que consigas más chats y matches. - Travel Mode: ¿Te mudás? ¿Estás viajando? Chateá con gente de otras lugares y recibí una cálida bienvenida 🧳 - Snooze Mode: Hacé tu perfil invisible durante el tiempo que quieras, no vas a perder ningún match.  - Velamos por vos: En Bumble no hay lugar para quien no respete a los demás y las normas de nuestro chat. No te preocupes, ¡estás en buenas manos! Pero, ¿cómo funciona Bumble? Nuestra red social te permite disfrutar del dating online y las relaciones como hasta ahora, pero de una manera más segura y respetuosa. Flirtear, buscar pareja y hacer amigos es más fácil con Bumble, pero acordate que las mujeres siempre dan el primer paso. Conexiones heterosexuales: Las mujeres disponen de 24 horas para iniciar un chat y los hombres de 24 horas para responder. Conexiones del mismo sexo: Tenés 24 horas para iniciar un chat, mientras que la otra persona cuenta con 24 horas para responder o, de lo contrario, la conexión vence.    Llevá Bumble al siguiente nivel 🚀 Bumble se puede descargar y usar de forma gratuita. Sin embargo, también ofrecemos un paquete de suscripción opcional (Bumble Premium) y servicios de pago de usos múltiples o únicos para los que no se requiere suscripción (Bumble Boost y Spotlight). Políticas de Privacidad y Términos de Uso: https://bumble.com/es/privacy https://bumble.com/es/terms

comments: ["It is a total waste of time and money. It does not matter if you have premium, you won't be receiving any matches at all (I had subscribed to the premium, still the same). It's like a window shopping app where you just keep scrolling and scrolling until you're satisfied without hoping to get anything. For once I thought this app could be genuine and I purchased the premium, but no, if all I had to do was left and right swipe people, I might have as well stayed on Tinder for free.", 'The UI is quite user friendly. But few things which can be improved on. 1. Message notification doesn\'t pop up a lot of times 2. Call notification doesn\'t pop up ever, plus call drops multiple times 3. Filter option doesn\'t work properly, for example if I choose age range 33-36, I still see people of age 23 4. Algo for common interest can be improved specially for best bees feed, I get best bees who want "Something Casual" while my preference is "Relationship"', 'I can not escape the feeling of a jacked up algorithm. One that puts people on the bottom despite their subscription in some sort of "lead with a carrot" business model. That or no one\'s on this app, and the app does not seem to want to take people who have not been on the app in months in the algorithm. Furthermore, there seems to be no quick, obvious, and easy way to end your subscription.', "I used the app for about one year and had a few decent dates out of it. However, as soon as my paid membership expired, literally overnight, I went from having zero people interested in me to 47, of course being prompted to go back to the paid version. Didn't change location or filters during that time, so obviously, they are manipulating the truth and the end user.", 'For an app that requires access to your location, you\'d think they\'d give you an accurate mileage estimate for people near you, but nope they can\'t be bothered to do that. Just saw someone who lives in the next state over from me and, according to Bumble, they\'re 85 miles away from me. However, when I enter the city on Google maps, it gives me a much more accurate mileage: 156 miles. That\'s a 71 mile difference, nearly double Bumble\'s "estimate."', 'The worst of all dating apps. Like Tinder, gives you options from ridiculous distances, especially if youre in rural areas. Most people are visitors from very far. The worst part is once youve swiped left on a potential match they are removed from your likes and you probably will never see them again."you\'ve missed a potential match" forever. Also they put the location at the bottom so you have to scroll the whole profile just to see the distance factor. Overall a very bad experience', "This app is ok but needs work. I canceled my premium. One of the big thing that must be added is letting me know when the last time a person logged on. That way I'm not wasting time on someone who hasn't logged on in a month. That's a waste of a swipe especially a super swipe. Also need to separate straight people from gay. As I have swiped on the wrong person and they get all offended. If these things were fixed I would keep logging in.", "I have emailed support multiple times about transferring my premium subscription from a previously deleted account to my new account and there has been absolutely no response from anyone in support. Unlike other dating apps that allow you to re-instate previously purchased subscriptions without having to email support (that doesn't respond to you anyway), Bumble just really need to sort its issues out.", "Terrible app! you have to pay for basic Things like just to see who liked you you can only see the people that complimented your profile and that's limited, You have to pay for everything like super swipes & to go back if you made a mistake. They took down one of my photos for going against community guide lines but it's a picture of me in a long dress no nudity nothing inappropriate. & whatever preferences youre allowed to choose (age and distance) doesn't narrow down the field", "Still an awful app, I've tried it multiple times and men never see their related matches. We get search results from 97 miles away from people who don't match our criteria. And you can tell even from the blurry images that you never see the people who actually do swipe on you. It's entirely designed to keep you swiping without any actual results. Don't waste your time", 'Waste of time and money, the location of people is totally hit and miss, when you do "match" with someone it is debatable if they are actually real or generated by the app to keep you interested. For an app that is meant to compliment your social circle/find people with similar interests and so on, no one actually talks. Might just stick with the old-fashioned way!', "All the other dating apps I get plenty of matches, but bumble is awful at what it's supposed to do. No matches, and because of the time limit to message you often miss the matches you do get. Pointless app and a waste of time. Edited, after the reply I received more likes than before after I left a review, strange, then they started to get less and Ive just realised the compliment feature has been removed. I think the free compliments were the only thing that made bumble worth using.", "Because you can't filter results by important categories like religion without paying, the app is essentially useless. You are forced to weed through thousands of profiles that aren't close to your value specifications. The profiles layout is also a mess, listing interests in a buckshot-style jumble where things like children, religion, age, location, etc are thrown into the mix randomly and you have to look around more to find it (those should be at the top of the list).", "I think it's more likely to get struck by lightning and win the lottery at the same time than get a match. It's way too easy to accidentally swipe left, and those swiped on can't come back, and the highlights cost 8 bucks each. Like, who even? Fix your app.", "What's the use of having the dating interface if you can't even contact/connect to a prospect without having to pay a bloody fee? And even then, even if you do want to spend on it, the chances of getting catfished is unbelievably high. The aspect of this side of the app is completely useless. I will give it props if you're using it for business networking purposes and works well if that is your ONLY objective. The dating interface is bonkers.", "it's very picky and decisive wanting you to spend money just like any other app. they shouldn't just give the option free to connect with anyone but they should make a lot easier if you want to say hello or block or do what you would like explicit or not. there's filters for everything. just make it all around app that everybody can use. it's 2023 and this is the longest run on sentence I've ever done. but we all know what we're looking for in the beginning and in the end and who may b in middle", 'It\'s just as bad if not worse than Tinder surprisingly. Customer service is 0/10. I can\'t get a hold of any humans to discuss my problems, I\'ve sent at least 10 emails. I get photos randomly taken down because they "violate" community standards according to the algorithm. I\'ve purchased the lifetime membership twice and, like anyone, deleted and reinstalled the app many times, but now I dont have the lifetime membership, and they won\'t fix it. Summary: All dating apps suck.', 'Bait and switched into "subscription". If I wanted to continue after the 1 month trial I agreed to paid for, I would have chosen a less expensive package. I cancelled the subscription and contacted support 20 minutes after charged, I had to open a PayPal case. 2 weeks later Bumble hasnt responsed. Bait and switch auto-subscriptions are theft. Ive lost $60 to this "free" app and have zero dates to show for it, just "content sellers" posting their Instagram and onlyfans.', 'Totally wast of time & Money, I have not received positive responses from the opposite gender. The 30-minute spotlight feature, promising up to 10x matches, did not help. People seem less active, making it challenging to find potential matches. Considering trying other apps, Bumble has not been useful recently. I do not recommend it based on my recent experiences.', "Bumble is useless without a premium subscription. All filters except age & distance are now locked behind a paywall, so rooting through all the bad matches to find someone is a chore. You only get 24 hours to respond to a match, otherwise you have to pay to rematch. And if you accidentally swipe left on someone you do want to match with, you have to pay to undo it. If the woman matches but doesn't start chatting within 24 hours, (Something that happens A LOT) the match disappears completely.", "Not sure how I feel about it. So far I like how the verification process goes and the app runs smooth but been on it for 2 weeks with premium and not worth it. You don't really get as much people due to the fact that the premium is expensive and also the notification when you do get someone doesn't really appear on either the app notification or email. Also anyone you've liked you can't tell if they even seen the like. Definitely needs more work for the cost.", "I like this app, in my opinion it' s very nice but it's just ridiculously expensive. probably the most expensive app I've tried. so I subscribed in different app although I still use the free features on Bumble. Some things could be better. don't like the fact that only match girls can do first move, think that's silly. I've been on a date with a girl and she complained that men never say anything, then I said we can't, first move has to be from girl.", "When you pay to upgrade and it run out. I have found that when you get likes the system doesn't match you with them. I wants you to upgrade. They then timed out and their gone. Don't pay for the upgrade or you'll just have to delete your account like I did. It should be above all, about finding a connection.", 'Having a limit on likes per day isn\'t a bad idea, but this app\'s limit is almost cartoonish. I can\'t spend more than a few minutes per 24 hours swiping without being told I need to pay 3 WHOLE DOLLARS to keep going. It\'s asinine. On top of that, almost everything else is locked behind paywalls. Though I do like that you can list your pronouns without having to first pick "man or woman." But that\'s just basic decency, not a feature', "I've been on Bumble for a few weeks now. Ended up paying for the boost, matched with someone who, for their prompt, asked me to verify my photo. Prior to this I had tried probably 20 times to verify, and was never able to. Yes I tried photos with just myself. Mimicking the pose, hand gestures, and even location exactly, but couldn't verify. Now I'm stuck on the verification screen, I'm being ignored by the support team. 0/5", "To the pros: fairly clean & simple UI, tho a bit outdated. Cons: gps based search, meaning swiping endlessly tons of people in proximity, including tourists & people in the airport and there's no way to filter out. And you have to scroll all way down to find out person is living somewhere else or doesn't disclose. So looks like tinder at this point and more oriented towards finding one night stand nearby. Exhausting & very disappointing experience for me and after a long time trying it, I'm out", "So there is a subscription model for 21 dollars a month, but this subscription does not come with the ability to see who likes you. For that, you'd need ANOTHER subscription 13 dollars more expensive than the regular subscription. To unlock seeing who likes you, you have to pay 35 bucks a month. That's gotta be an accident, right? Why would this feature not be in the regular subscription?", "Don't buy the spot lights!!!! The app will self activate them and email support stopped trying to help! I tried just not being on for a couple days till subscription weekly one was added when I did log on it has already used it and times out! Yes I emailed them and they tried a couple time but stopped helping. Lost 5 so far. And they are not doing anything to help. Very disappointed in you guys. I'm done I've cancelled the subscription and not trying to get your help when you just blow it off.", "It's...ehhh. My issues are the inability to filter out poly/ENM profiles looking for unicorns, continuing to get likes from men when I am a lesbian, the constant message ads and empty notifications, and the high cost of premium. Been using it for a few months now, met one potential person but I'm demoralized. I won't renew my subscription.", 'I tried several times to get my picture verified, including taking a picture, posting it, and then without moving, taking the same picture in the verify area. They still said I could not be verified. I contacted customer service about it, and my app got stuck on the verify photo page and would not leave that page. I then contacted customer service two more times about it and still stuck. It would be nice to at least be able to try the app out.', "Well developed but core functionality is behind a paywall, and there's no incentive to pay for an app that feels dead. Honestly it looks great but actually seeing who has matched you is behind a pricy paywall, so it's a dice roll as to whether two people see each other, and this makes the limited ability to like people (an otherwise good feature) greatly lower the ceiling on chances of matching. People have moved onto other apps.", 'The app needs work on how it recognizes and interacts with phone media. It\'s difficult to get it to recognize videos & it has double standards when it comes to photos and videos. The app allows the most pixelated pictures you\'ll ever see; however, it won\'t let me upload perfectly fine videos due to "low quality" (they\'re not), wrong dimensions (huh?), or not being shot on my phone (really?). So far, it\'s not very user-friendly.', "Swear this app is a con. I have 9 so say 'matches waiting for me'. I just used a boost and spent the full 30 minutes swiping to see if I would get anywhere with any of them (get rid of or properly match with them) and I didn't come across a single one of these people. It is so blatantly a scam just to make people feel like they have no option but to pay to see more etc etc...", "The customer service for Bumble is absolutely terrible!! I have contacted them over 10 times in a two week span and Bumble has not replied to ANY of my inquiries. My account is stuck on photo verification and I cannot access any othet part of my account. I am currently paying for the Premium option as well. Don't use this app - they dont care about you at all.", "Bought premium (little under $9/wk because it was on sale). Was good at first but right now it's not letting me view profiles of people who have liked me (I can see their picture but when I click on them a blank square comes up instead of their profile). Literally the only reason I bought premium was so I could see people who liked me, so it's very frustrating that the feature stopped working. Hopefully it will work again soon. Edit: also not letting me send or view messages right now. :/", 'Very good idea but poor efficiency; is a pity that girls have only 24 hrs to establish a contact... Also, you should put more filters: for example: eyes color, hair color, etc., and stablish options to search by that criteria; for exemple, if I only want to meet people without kids or blonde girls or short (or tall) girls, be able to find those persons easily.', "The premium option is nice, maybe a little expensive for what you get. My issue is that with the premium subscription you run out of people within your filters. But if you're subscription ends you will run out of likes before you run out of people within your filters. Things don't add up properly.", "Even after having premium it doesn't let's text to someone who liked my profile. It clearly showed in best bees match. But it didn't let me text. What a pathetic app. They just want you to keep browsing and keep paying for super swipes or compliments even after buying premium. You will get nothing here. I think they just got some profiles when they launched the app. Might be no longer active because this app doesn't let people text even after liking from both sides.", "Don't recommend, I submitted seven verification photos exactly the way my profile poster was & when I tried to get customer support I've gotten zero response back other than them saying they verified who I am but to try to keep verifying my picture that matches. I paid for the week premium & the app is still stuck in the verification process & will not let me move forward. & they're still trying to charge me of subscription fee. The email I get back from customer service is a auto generated", "Horrible experience - they aren't responding to my emails to restore my lifetime premium membership. Been writing to them since two weeks to restore the unlimited premium subscription that I bought previously, no response to whatsoever, just an auto reply that we've received your email. The worst customer team ever. I don't even know if they'll fix this for me, but I'll continue to follow up."]

title: Pet Perfect - Puppy & Dog Care
description:
Recognized as one of the Best Apps of 2022 by Google Play🚀

Embark on a Journey to provide the best care to your Doggo 🐶.

Get easy to follow, daily schedule of activities, curated by experts.

As a dog parent, we know you are tired🤔 of wasting time looking for info according to your pets age & breed. It’s hard to keep a track of their daily key activities like feeding, walking, bathing, brushing, etc. Many a time you can’t remember the vaccination & deworming dates📅. Don’t know what steps to take for your doggo’s perfect upbringing? Because your pet can’t tell you what they need! We seldom seek the opinion of experienced Pet Parents & Veterinarians. But in reality, we need one place to learn all the best dog health care practices.

Pet Perfect is your one-stop companion for everything you’ll need to make the most of your furry friend. The best companion for your pets, curated with love and passion😇.

🐾Pet Journey- feature provides pet parents with step-by-step tasks on every stage of dog life according to your dogs age and breed.

🐾Pet Engagement - Have fun with your furball with our vivid range of perplexing dog sounds🔉

🐾Vaccination & Deworming Tracker - Get automated reminders for your dog's vaccination and deworming dates with just a single tap. 💉

🐾Dog Community - Get your queries resolved by Experts and Veteran Pet Parents & make new friends who share our love of doggo🐕.

Check our website here:- https://www.petperfect.in/

Also, do follow our Social Media Handles:-

Instagram:- https://www.instagram.com/petperfect_ig/

Facebook:- https://www.facebook.com/petperfect2021

P.S. Currently, we support the following pet types: Dogs

title: FeeDog - Raising Dog
description:
You can heal by feeding dogs and watching cute things!
Get a cute dog, Lucky, Rack, and various dogs!
When the dog grow up, they help Lucky fight ghosts together.
You can dress them in cute clothes, too!

# Good food is eaten automatically if you stay still.

# Bad food can be hit by touching the screen when it gets close.

# Attack ghosts with bad food!
- If you touch bad food, bad food flies to the ghost and damages it.
- If you feed good food, it will restore the ghost.

# The ghost attacks Lucky after a certain period of time.

# Raise Lucky's level in the store with the star coin you got after defeating the ghost.
- A stronger Lucky can hunt a stronger ghost.

# If you collected Gem, you can meet the dog through the dog basket!
- When you feeding milk to your dog , Lucky gets stronger, too!
- When the dog grows up, it can combine with Lucky and Rack to fight!
- Dress your dog in cute clothes!

# Game Tip!
- The more you keep the combo, the more star coins you get.
- Angel buffs cover up one mistake.


# FeeDog is requesting these permissions to store and load game data.

• READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE
• WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE

FeeDog is a game without a server and does not use your information separately.

FeeDog web page: http://www.facebook.com/qssumstudio

comments: ["Its a pretty nice game, overall. Its got adorable graphics, and the tutorial is mostly understandable. It even teaches you a little about what dogs can and cannot eat ^.^ The gems can be hard, but are not impossible to get. Although, its hard to get a large sum without watching a lot of ads ~w~ Other than that, there isnt much to do. The 'walk' can get a little repetative, and I would like other things to do. Theres room for improvement, but its a nice game =3 a keeper for me", "This is one of the few games I can play without turning my wifi and data off due to ads. The few ads there are don't interrupt gameplay or make noise. The art style and little animations are very cute. There's an option to buy stars but it's still possible to get them in game (At least a hundred every day) and everything else can be earned in-game as well.", "It's a very cute and fun game to play :). I love how we learn about how to treat real life dogs with the album descriptions, and I'd love to see more of that. The artstyle is very cute and the dogs are adorable! The gameplay is very fun and very chill, and I love the fusion feature. It'd be cool if we could get other dogs more easily, as well as a bigger variety of dogs. After you unlock Lack and reach level 100 with him there's not much left to do other than getting more stars to get more dogs.", "This app is amazing - 11/10 would recommend. It's great; engaging and cute, with an amazing, simple, and easy to understand system that doesn't have the overbearing complexity that certain games do. It's great and relaxing, you get enough rewards and new things to really feel that you're accomplishing things, and it's fun - a rare but great find. Also, I love the way that you get gems, but the only thing I wish is that there was a way you could get more, even after you've watched the ads", "I have had this game on every device for years because you can play it offline. My no1 major issue is it forces you to replay the same 10 stages or so over and over again to grind for money so you can power up to move forward. Otherwise you'll eventually be forced to stop by an enemy you could not possibly defeat despite a perfect score on everything else. Wish there was an endless mode that didn't kick you from the game unless you messed up too many times.", 'This game is actually really helpful if you have ADHD and need to listen to informational videos or lectures but need to do something with your hands+visual stimulation as to not get bored or overwhelmed. Its just in depth enough where I can focus on what people are saying without thinking too hard about actions in game that I get distracted. Extremely useful for me personally!', "The ads don't interrupt gameplay, it's really fun and easy to learn how to play, and progress is at your own pace. I loved this game-- I first played it years ago, and got it again a few months ago for nostalgia. The new Halloween update annoys me, though. It's extremely buggy and made it nearly impossible to perform lucky hits.", 'this is a good game to play when your bored and need to pass the time! its a bonus that the chararacters and art style are adorable! there are a few things that i would like to suggest though. like a easier way to get rainbow stars and making the game have consistency of the controls actually working after a hour or so of playing. overall, the game is very fun and very adorable! ^^', "I've known this game for years, after I changed my phone four times. This is the cute and best game at that time, which can I finish after some time and now I've decided to re-install and start all over again. Though, I wish the dev could add more things and keep updating the game so I can enjoy it a little longer after finishing the main story.", "Could be improved, game speed is too fast to start with. The tips flash across the screen and nowhere else to read them. Instructions are too quick, no way to pause the instructions... Some features don't work right yet. But good idea, just needs some work. Very cute style.", 'A very simple but charming game! The dogs are adorable, and the gameplay, although very straightforward, is entertaining! I found myself completely in love with this game the second I opened it. No in your face ads, glitchy controls, or pixelated graphics. The art is adorable and the story is a little cherry on top of this amazing game.', "I love the art, and story. Its fun to discover new achievements, and just play in general. There is little to no ads which is a huge plus in my opinion and a really good time saver. So in all I would definately recommend this cute app to anyone who's looking for an easy easy way to kill time.", 'I like that the microtransactions are not as obnoxious as in other games. The in game currency is earned easily and quickly, watching ads is afaik entirely optional, but you earn currency by doing so. The transitions between power levels are smooth and earning gold for upgrades only turns more intense in later levels (ca. At 350 or so), but feels entirely appropriate.The graphics are adorable and the achievements (gold stars) are nicely integrated and unlock environmental interactions', "GReaT game! so cute and simple, great music, sounds and visuals. SO, CUte, great variation in dogs interactions and reactions! and i couldn't help but notice the great (i forgot word. as below)! it keeps from getting boring and monotinous by the varition in like everything, game speed, (great strategic introduction of lack). 6 stars for above and beyond! (ps. would like for there to be a toggle off for the red 'lucky' thing.?)", "So adorable and addicting. 😍 Although I think it would be nice if it had more to the game than just feeding the dogs. Like maybe a neighborhood or something that you can walk around and collect and gain coins from feeding other people's dogs and playing fetch with the dogs or something. Just add something new, it might even be more addicting and adorable!!", "its one of the best games on my phone! super duper cute! its really a satisfying sound when the ghosts get hit. but there is one thing that kind of bugs me but only one thing I swear. why can't you get the rainbow star gems easier? I mean my poor puppy hasn't been able to level up forever! but I'm cool with that. oh and love the cool features like the comic strips and walking the dog!", "The game become very addictive when you get the hang of it, the art style is very cute. And the level up system is pretty simple too. But when you fully complete the game, it become boring and you're stuck in a loop where you just hit the bomb and eat the foods forever.", "To put it simply, BEST. GAME. EVER. Oh, where to start? It has dogs and puppies, it's VERY addicting and a great time killer when people like myself who don't have many things to do throughout the day can enjoyably play on their phone, it's graphics are great and simple, not to mention cute, the levels are still challenging even at level 200 and beyond (Like I said, I have a lot of free time and my only hobby is playing video games.) And even BEYOND what I just said, it's kept me coming back. :)", "I like this game, although I have a few issues with it. The upgrades get so expensive and pretty annoying. It's honestly a pain getting the rainbow stars to afford anything. I don't wanna spend an hour watching 25 ads for some of 'em, idk about you. I don't understand how to get the yellow stars either tbh. I wish there was some background on what the things you're fighting are, like why do they like dog food? And it has kind of bad wording at the start too. Other than that, it's pretty good.", "Really cute and lovely, a fun and addicting game! The only problem is that it gets boring over time if you are done with all story parts with both dogs and have all the puppies; there's nothing to achieve anymore. Being able to unlock more dogs to play with would be amazing.", "Very fun and enjoyable game. Whenever i need to add new apps to my phone this is one of my first ideas. It's educational teaching you about what figs and cats can and cannot eat. And the gameplay mechanics are simple but can become very challenging. All and all a great game.", "A very cute game, if you like dogs this is the game for you! The only reason I gave it a 4/5 stars is because you can't watch as many ads as you wish for, you can only watch a certain amount a day, and because you can get thigs out of ghe ads its very frustrating, at list for me.", "It's adorable and time consuming. The graphics are so cute and so is the music. The story, along with the concept, is so unique and portrayed in such simply effective ways. Completely recommend for people who have an appreciation for wacky and cute stories.", "It's a good game but what's the most annoying part about it is the hitboxes are wonky and it has a strange delayed lag to it which makes you have to tap the projectiles twice or they just completely ignore the fact you tapped them and end your game immediately. This has happened to me too many times and takes away from the relaxing cute aspect of the game.", "The game is actually a great time-killer. It's pretty straightforward, and you don't necessarily have to do purchases to win. I don't enjoy binging ads to get crystals, but at least they're not invasive of the gamespace. Overall, enjoyable experience.", "Adorable, some of the stuff is vague (I imagine it's just the language barrier) but it's easy to figure out. The rewards are fair and not near- impossible to obtain. A great, cute little game to play to pass the time.", "I loved this game so much!! I love the style, storyline, dogs, and pretty much everything about it! I did see some questions, though. The Touch Evade can be accomplished by tapping the dog repeatedly during walks (outside of levels). Although I love the game, it struck me as odd that you can't really seem to level up the puppies without milk. :)", "Its a really cute addictive game to play! Playing as two different dogs, both are extremely cute and have their own things to swipe at enemies. I'd highly recommend this game since its quick and easy to get behind, and fun to play to pass the time!", 'I remember playing this game when I was younger, it was and still is a lot of fun! The art style is adorable and the "album" is just the funniest. My only problem is that I\'ve noticed a few glitches when you go to "walk with the dog." Like with the red ball in the tree, it disappears halfway through the animation.', "Very simple but very cute game. If you're looking for something mechanically deep you'll have to look elsewhere but if you want a game with adorable visuals that you can play for a couple minutes without it demanding you give up months of your life, this is a great pick.", "Not too many ads, clean, silly, good graphics, honestly there isn't much to say. It's simple, and yet it never gets boring. Broken language from here and there, but it's translated. Totally reccomend :)", "It's a super cute little game with a repetitive yet good feeling mini game at it's core. I especially enjoy the art style and collection of events that can be occurred and catalouged. It also has no ads that directly stop your game and the placement of the sidebar ads have yet to be cumbersome", "Very fun game! I have played it on and off for the past 4ish years and am still not bored everytime I return. It weirdly isn't syncing up my achievements with my google play thing, but that might be an issue on my end. Over all I really appreciate the little snip bits of why the bad foods are bad for dogs. I think that's clever to add.", "Such a cute and adorable game. All of the dogs are cute and so are the animations. It's really smooth. One complaint I have is its too easy to collect coins. Another is it's too hard to collect stars. Stars let's you buy goodies like milk for puppies and more puppies. There's only two ways to collect stars: ads and walk the dog. Walk the dog is cute, but you barely get stars from it. I wish you could do more with it. Other than that, its a awesome game. So addicting.", "Very cute! I played this game like crazy a few years ago and went to revisit it, but I can't find an option to restore my progress. I made it really far and had a few different dogs, so I'm wondering if there might be a way to restore what I had? If not I'd be cool with just replaying, but if possible I'd love to get that back.", 'Really fun and cute, the graphics are simple and the gameplay itself is easy to understand. Also has interesting facts about dogs. Also the ads are not shown during actual gameplay only in the house or walking the dog.', "it's a really adorable and fun app. The animals are so cute and the game is really addicting! The only thing I would say is that you can only watch so many ads to get stars before it cuts you off for the day, and I don't think it's very necessary. It's not easy to get stars unless you watch the ads. But other than that, great app!", "A really lovely game. It's a simple time waster with a cute and well tied together aesthetic. The main gimmick is tapping the screen to bat away bad foods while letting the dog eat the good foods. The banner ads don't interfere with game play and ads can be watched for paid currency. You can get around $4 worth of currency per day through that and check in rewards without spending any money. Main negatives are poor English translations and a lack of explanations for other game mechanics.", "very cute! the game ain't hard to understand even if you miss what the tips says or notes that pop up, Which I do find they go away to fast for me to read but if it was big issue it's always a easy fix. The game style is adorable of corse. I like it and it's great!", "This is quite possibly one of the best (and cutest) games on the play store. After playing 400+ stages in only 5 days I can confirm that this game is just as addictive as it is cute. Although this game is originally in a different language the translation is well done and you barely see any ads. Even the premium currency is easy to get without spending a penny. I can't say anything bad about this game. l just wish there was a little more story. I can't wait to see more from the developers!"]

title: iris: Your personal Dating AI
description:
We know how it feels to believe true love was not meant for you. 
To sense that the relationship you deserve is out of reach.

If you’re like us, you’ve been disappointed with typical online dating apps. You’ve wondered if endless swiping can 
ever lead to a relationship based on feelings of mutual attraction. We know you want to love and be loved. Still, it’s 
wrong that most dating apps make meeting someone feel like a roll of the dice.

Iris Dating was born from our founder’s frustration with typical dating apps and a desire to create an experience closer 
to how special relationships begin in real life. 

That cute guy in the coffee shop; the beautiful woman on the train — we’ve all been smitten by someone at first sight. 
That’s the power of attraction. Iris Dating applies Artificial Intelligence to understand who you are attracted to 
and uses that understanding to present you with matches to people who also are attracted to someone like you.

Our team of passionate love geeks has put over 100,000 hours into understanding what drives attraction between two 
people. We’ve helped thousands overcome the typical shortcomings of online dating and meet a partner who wants to 
build a successful relationship. Mutually.

We are committed to helping you find someone you share a genuine attraction with so you can stop feeling like you 
have to settle in a relationship. The process is simple — 

(1) Download the Iris Dating app; 
(2) Teach our AI engine your preferences, and; 
(3) See your matches based on mutual attraction

It’s time to stop wasting your time endlessly swiping and find reciprocal love. Our integrated ChatGPT assistant will help you build an attention-grabbing bio and unleash your personality. Say goodbye to boring dating profiles and experience effortless and personalized dating with this innovative technology!

POSSIBILITIES START HERE
“Met a few good friends so far and the recent match... WOW! Most successful date I have had in years! This week will 
be the fifth time I see her in five weeks. See where this goes. If anyone is tired of typical online dating, iris sure can fix 
that problem.”
— Trent Silvernail

 “Hi! I just wanted to let you know because of your app, I have a Valentine’s date tonight! Thank you so much. I really 
like the way your app is built. And the interface is very user-friendly and unique.”
— Chi

Follow us for dating and relationship tips: https://eq.irisdating.com/
Free to download and use.
View our Terms of Use https://www.irisdating.com/terms-of-use
View our Privacy Policy https://www.irisdating.com/privacy-policy
You must be at least 18 years old to use

comments: ["Sorted through roughly 1,900+ matches... and maybe a dozen or so were in the US?! Distance filter only works for the discovery tab, which is empty 99% of the time. I understand the concept, but it just doesn't work. I don't think I had more than 2 or 3 potential matches that were even in my state! I reached out to the developer and they were no help...", "I've been using Iris for 6 months up to level 123, each level is 100 swipes. It's worthless. The AI still doesn't learn my attraction, gives profiles I keep telling it to pass, and it throws more awful at me, never getting above 80% confidence. It seems to only analyze positively liking a profile, ignoring passing on profiles. Buttons are hard to press. The app uses fullscreen splash pages with timer delays that you can't swipe away. I've had 1 chat. Profiles aren't even English half the time.", 'I don\'t trust any app which forces me to take a "\'selfie\'" before you\'re even allowed to use it. Are we all vapid teenage girls to you or what? Anyway, the app has potential, but there\'s not enough filters to make it worthwhile and almost all selection is done based on superficial choosing of faces. I kept getting non-English profiles and non-straight women, which I have no interest in, but there\'s no way to filter out these bad options. Way more needs to be added to the app to make it decent.', "To many worldwide matches. I don't want that. Too many unfinished profiles! They shouldn't be including those if they have only put up a picture. AI doesn't learn. In order to switch back from global to local, I have to scan many profiles first. How dumb is that?", 'I\'m on a galaxy 23 ultra. This trash app won\'t let me access my Google photos or any of my albums. It only has options of "recent" photos that are up to a week old and "albums" which in reality is just one picture that\'s not even in an album and is in fact my most recent photo.', "I have the same complaint as many others. Even though some of the matches might be good, the distance is ridiculous. What's the point of having a distance feature when it still keeps matching you to people from another country persistently. I've contacted customer support and they explained about the levels, so I gave it some time. Now I'm at level 💯 and the trust has been stuck at 80% since I was at level 60. It is still as bad as level 1", "This app is pretty easy to use once you figure it out, but there are two main problems. Firstly, half of the bios I am reading are not in English, the only language I am able to read. True attraction or not, I want to be able to understand my partner, so please add a language filter. Secondly, despite being a man, I was suggested a straight man in Discover. Now I feel as if I might have been liking straight men. Please make it so straight men don't see gay men and vice versa. Thank you.", 'You should allow a person to say they "like everything" about a profile. Some of the ones that come up I like the face, interests, and physique. I don\'t know how to pick a "most important" to help the algorithm. Declining someone for "too far" or similar does not invalidate all of the other good qualities. Hopefully that is clear for the algo. You could add a "rating review matrix" as like an advanced mode. I\'d gladly click a few boxes to give detailed ranking data of "liked face, physique, et', "The app feel empty and kinda pointless. I've had this app for at least 6 months and I have yet to even receive notion of a like, let alone a match. I've had much more success with matching on other apps with a fraction of the time. On here you're just swiping right and left to increase your level (which I have no idea does and I'm currently at 17).", 'Only suggests people in totally different states... I finally gave in and liked someone it suggested and got a message saying "oops! It looks like they are too far away!" Like I did it intentionally. This app is not good and filtering searches doesn\'t make it any better or more accurate. Then it wants you to pay for this lack of service. No thanks.', "I'm at 78% confidence but it still brings up profiles that have aspects that I already stated I don't like, it doesn't seem to acknowledge my preferences and just keeps shoving individuals that I have no interest in. The app needs its AI looked at because it isn't really working", "The best of the Worst is still the worst. All the rejects of the gene pool are the only options to choose from. Decent people are not coming to this app. They're all weird looking unattractive frogs. Horrible app. The AI can only choose the best of the ugly frogs. That's not really a choice now is it. Pointless app.", "The app does indeed help you find your ideal matches, but all your matches are subscribed with their premium service, so before you could even talk to anyone, you have to pay up first. It is a good one, but just to set expectations be ready to pay for it. I'm uninstalling for now, because other apps are free and I'll just install this one later on when I can to pay for it.", "It says it filters according to your preference yet they keep feeding the ones I don't like. Even geographically speaking at least. They keep showing the ones from another country ... I can't match them anyways without a fee and even then the chances of meeting them are astronomically lower. The face recognition is tacky and a hack. It doesn't REALLY filter towards your preferencce", "I would have said 4 stars, maybe even 5 in the past since I made a few meaningful connections, but quickly it began to only suggest people in the Philippines LOL. ( I have filters set to distance: closest First). Now there is no way to cancel the monthly subscription within the app and no instructions to do so. It offered a lot for free before that, so maybe you'll have a good run in the short-term but beware of paying money until they get their problems fixed.", "Clunky, laggy UI. Buttons behave like they dont actually do anything, then the response happens later on. Matches, conversations, and sent messages go in and out of existence. The swiping like or pass mode is often interrupted with erroneous 'Congratulations for swiping' message animations that hijack the app until a splah screen animation is done playing. These pop up animations add nothing to the experience, its almost like they added it as a prank to be disruptive.", 'Iris has a great freemium model that offers a premium pass at a reasonable price that most people can actually afford. And maybe the best part? NO ADS WHATSOEVER! This app stands out to me because of its revolutionary approach to mate selection, and I hope the development team will continue to refine the attraction algorithm. Iris has what it takes to become a major player in the dating app landscape.', "My favorite app ever! Use it if you're open minded about distance. I'm a world traveler so not a problem for me. I actually met someone almost immediately after being on the app and we clicked! (I never find a great connection with online dating so this app worked for me!) The AI technology is amazing! It learns what you like and sends you really good matches. Better than any other app ever! I highly recommend it if you're serious about finding something serious! Thank you Iris!❤️", 'App keeps saying "Oops Something Went Wrong" and won\'t open. It\'s kind of frustrating when you have notifications saying you have messages and matches.', 'This app use to be one of the best but since it has removed the thing to like foreigners is worst as now i can not even like someone who likes me back. Please make this app how it use to be show us adds everyone can not pay the money.', 'i can\'t use the app i even restart my phone and uninstall it already, cause i thought my phone went nuts, but it\'s not, it keep sayin "something went wrong, please try again" pls fix this asap. ( the issue repeated i can\'t used the app) 😕', 'I enjoyed my time on the app until I got an error saying "oops-Something went wrong, Try again"...Is the app now broken because after that point it just freezes up or goes back to the same message..what does that mean?', "This app has such penitential but I'm already level 9 going through all the profiles I can possibly rate and not one match on the sight but one girl had her insta in her bio on and I could add her from there but it's just frustrating to have to matches and you keep trying", "I paid for the monthly subscription, but now I can't sign in the app. I've tried reinstalling the app but that doesn't work either. Don't waste your money on the app.", 'This app is great. The only thing I would suggest is a range function. You can sort by distance but it still gives me profiles really far away, I feel as though selecting "this person is too far from me" doesn\'t narrow down the range at all. Everything else about it I like a lot, though.', 'Would like a way to log out but not delete profile People are being too harsh with reviews! You CAN filter by location in the "discover" section, where picks are not limited by the AI. You can also set a distance limit in settings! The AI feature is great. The population has grown since I was here last. Keep recommending Iris around, people! I\'ve always had a hard time finding guys I\'m attracted to- idk why. Even conventionally attractive guys not my type often, again idk why. This app is great.', "Have 2 likes in profile currently but the algo never sends there profile in my swipe list , I am tired tbh.😞 Editting this ...... The likes that I got never search my algo why it is that, if they don't arrive in my swipe list , how can I get match 21 likes on me are getting wasted....", 'This app is full of bots . You dont belive me take a screen shot of one of those beautiful women/men that just liked u and google search image and 99.99% of time its a stock photo from a paid site', "Garbage app they run a gimmick of claiming to run AI to help you match while majority of time they wont even allow You to upload photos you want half the time it will claim it cant see your face its just an absolute joke of an app you'll waste one whole day trying to set up an account and profile.", "This app might be good, but I can't get past phase 3 of the training. It always ends up with a white screen and nothing else. Even if I opt to retrain, I keep ending up with that white screen and at 95%. Not sure how this is different from other apps if the AI part is wonky and unable to be trained.", 'I\'ve just now completed the beginning section where I\'m shown random "stock" photos and I personally have always found myself attracted to both genders so I was shown photos of both men & women. I\'m not exaggerating at all... 😱🌀🤯🌬️🤯🌪️💥🔥💯 ( Emojis 2 Say) This app is incredibly..Mind Blowing !! I was told this app picks up on your individual preferences & the final section photos picking like ,maybe ,or pass on I found 96%/100% were likes 1%maybe ,3% passes. Amazing Odds I say! MUST TRY', "Such a dumb app. This AI is a hoax. How would the algorithm for attractiveness work if you can't filter language???!!! You might find someone attractive but you'll have to unlike them because you can't understand their language. So stupid. It limits your choices to find someone nearby which defeats the purpose because if you can find someone nearby, you wouldn't need the app in the first place. 🤦\u200d♀️", 'Very unique app but still a work in progress. I\'m willing to match with anyone that fits my "type" globally, but most women in the US want locals.. So 100% of my matches after a month are in the Phillipines, Russia, or India. The majority of the AI picks are still not great even after reaching level 120, and my "confidence rating" has seemingly maxed out at 80% because it hasn\'t changed in weeks. That said, I\'m still intrigued by the concept so I\'m sticking with it in hopes it keeps improving.', 'I\'ve used this app for about 8 months now. I\'ve had a number of conversations, tho most ladies are states or continents away. My main problem is that it constantly tells me i have seen "most" new members for my area for months now. Even if i get notifications saying girls within 100 miles of me liked me (cause i paid to see that). I want the app to be fixed and show me more local women. Thats the reason my rating is only 2 stars. At the time of writing im level 264. That is not an accomplishment', "Third edit: App is a waste of time, unless you want to talk to people you will not ever meet outside your country, because thats all you'll likely get. Level 181 out of boredom. I live in a major metropolitan area and it's rare I see anyone from my state. I like the app UI design and no real ads. People want local, because we're all busy locally, but you're probably not going to find that here.", "So I am over level 120 which means I've gone through over 12000 profiles (since you need to rate 100 profiles to level up). I have had 16 matches. Of those 16, only one has ever messaged me back and they immediately ghosted. If your dating AI has a success rate worse that 0.1% then it's safe to assume it's trash. Oh, and I paid for the app so this is the best experience they offer too. Sad.", "only 2 stars cause their local functionality does not work, when asking the support team got a semi condesinding reply saying i wasn't in the right tab (which i was) and that i wasn't using the local functionality, which as of sending the message i wasnt but had been untill prompted into using the global on. However it didnt matter regardless of local being on and being in the correct tab still shows no one close, if they just said no one close go global would be fine, but nope", "This app is better than any other dating app I've ever used. You basically train an AI to tailor your tastes in people. It does take time for it to recognize what people want, but that's normal. I'm level 71 and my Iris picks are at 80% I also chose to find some picture online from Google, which you can upload I think 20 of them. It helps train your AI even quicker. At first I wasn't getting any matches, then as I leveled up I got alot. 10/10 dating app", 'Set up for matching involves asking what I choose based on looks only. Since this is not how I date, this is a failed app system to me.', 'App seems promising. It would be nice to have in the options for why you didn\'t like a profile "Has kids". A lot of people don\'t want to date single parents. No hate on them, some people are fine with it. But the AI should identify if you like kids based on your ratings and allow you to filter against that by a special pass preference.']

title: Hundeo: Puppy & Dog Training
description:
🐶 Dog & Puppy Training Made Easy 🐕
Don't have a dog trainer or puppy training school with you right now? No problem! Hundeo offers you step-by-step video instructions on the most important topics that a digital dog obedience school can offer you in your pocket. We guide you from puppy to senior with the right content.

300+ Tricks, Games, Recipes and Courses.
Discover a wide range of tricks, games, and recipes for dogs. Get inspiration for your next training session and have fun together. In this app, you can find for example these course topics: Basic Commands, Puppy Basics (Walking the Pup, Potty House Training, Bite inhibition, Puppy Nutrition, Puppy Games, Puppy Commands), Leash Training, Recall Masterclass, How to ignore other dogs on walks, How to behave during a visit, Clicker Course, Dog Impulse control Guide, Health Check at Home, Raw Food Diet, Muzzle Trainer, Calm at Office, New Year's Eve Training, Stop your dog from eating random things, Stop Barking Trainer or Stay Alone Course for Dogs.

Step by Step to Your Goal
We guide you to your goal with our interactive video tutorials.
The tutorials are designed so that you can be successful with just 5 minutes of training a day. It reminds you of your training and when you train successfully, you get a great trophy for your virtual trophy case. In addition to dog training methods, you will also find great activities in the form of pet games and recipes.

Anytime, Anywhere - At Your Own Pace
Out in the park or garden with no reception? No problem. You can download content and use it offline.

New Daily
Daily free quizzes, tricks, games, recipes and courses carefully selected for you. Tailored to you and your breed. (We have 285 dog breeds like Labrador, French Bulldog, Pug, Doberman, Chihuahua)

Playfully to Success
To keep you motivated, you get new challenges every day and earn flames and trophies. 

Individual Profile
Create a profile for your puppy, dog, or even multiple pets and keep track of what you have accomplished and what you still need to practice.

Connect With Others
Have you learned some cool dog or puppy tricks and want to compare yourself with others? Invite your friends or other members of our community to compare your achievements and watch videos of other dogs and puppies.

Your Favorites
Keep track and create your own favorites list for easy access.

Clicker and Whistle Always With You
With a clicker, you always have the right tone with you. A clicker is the most efficient way to teach your puppy tricks and exercises.

Trusted
This app was developed in collaboration with professional dog experts and pet trainers. You can be sure that the exercises will really help you.

Support
If you have any questions about Hundeo or your account, please contact our customer support: support@hundeo.com

Hundeo Plus Membership
To unlock all the features, you can upgrade to ‘hundeo Plus’ and choose between the following subscriptions:
1 month
1 year

Terms and Conditions: https://www.hundeo.com/en/toc/
Privacy policy: https://www.hundeo.com/en/contact/data-protection/
